India Allows Companies to Borrow in Yuan, Places $1 Billion Cap

-- B y   A n t o   A n t o n y
-- 
2011-09-15T09:24:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/india-allows-companies-to-borrow-in-yuan-places-1-billion-cap.html
India  allowed local companies to
borrow in yuan, with a total cap of $1 billion, after several
firms sought the facility, R. Gopalan, secretary in the
Department of Economic Affairs in the  finance ministry , told
reporters in  New Delhi  today.  Infrastructure companies and those buying capital goods
will benefit from this step, he said, adding borrowers need to
get approval from regulators before raising yuan funds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anto Antony in New Delhi at 
 aantony1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sam Nagarajan at 
